  {
    "id": "200662070448291_1555117793290493",
    "message": "Many hands make light work!  We've never picked spruce tips in April before, but this year is special.  Spruce tips are a traditional substitute for hops in beer, bringing both citrus and pine-y flavors.  Look for this beer on tap in a month or so--it's a seasonal favorite.  #drinklocal #sprucetips \nVisit Coshocton, Ohio! @visitcoshocton Ohio Craft Beer @ohiocraftbeer Northeast Ohio Craft Beverage News @neo_craft_brewery_news",
